1
00:00:02,171 --> 00:00:05,038
Modern advertising is saturated

2
00:00:05,038 --> 00:00:07,506
with humanistic sloganeering.

3
00:00:07,859 --> 00:00:09,658
And what do I mean by that?

4
00:00:09,658 --> 00:00:11,955
Like Nike, “Just do it.”

5
00:00:12,124 --> 00:00:14,166
[Nike, L'Oreal and Me]

6
00:00:14,166 --> 00:00:17,342
What does that mean,
‘Just do it’?

7
00:00:17,342 --> 00:00:20,536
It implies there is 
some conscience you have,

8
00:00:20,536 --> 00:00:23,244
some self–restraint,

9
00:00:24,712 --> 00:00:26,864
an internal process you go through

10
00:00:26,864 --> 00:00:29,478
before you decide to do something.

11
00:00:29,478 --> 00:00:32,541
They’re saying,
“Don’t listen to it, don’t think about it,

12
00:00:32,541 --> 00:00:35,362
just do it!”

13
00:00:36,442 --> 00:00:38,524
Why?

14
00:00:38,524 --> 00:00:41,413
I have a series of ads
that answer this question.

15
00:00:41,413 --> 00:00:45,523
So, Nike makes that proposal,
who gives the answer?

16
00:00:45,523 --> 00:00:50,921
L’Oreal,
“Because I’m worth it.”

17
00:00:51,266 --> 00:00:52,504
Why should I just do it?

18
00:00:52,504 --> 00:00:56,631
Because I’m worth it,
that’s why.

19
00:00:57,392 --> 00:01:00,638
But of all the ads I ever saw,

20
00:01:00,638 --> 00:01:03,651
the most blatant,

21
00:01:04,745 --> 00:01:12,717
naked assertion
of humanistic sloganeering

22
00:01:12,717 --> 00:01:16,669
was from a company
whose slogan was,

23
00:01:16,669 --> 00:01:21,284
“Total indulgence. Zero guilt.”

24
00:01:22,465 --> 00:01:24,953
It was about Weight Watchers.

25
00:01:24,953 --> 00:01:26,840
It doesn’t matter
what it was about,

26
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:29,718
but they had the audacity 
to make that their slogan,

27
00:01:29,718 --> 00:01:32,835
“Total indulgence. Zero guilt.”

28
00:01:32,835 --> 00:01:37,254
No conscience,
just indulge without conscience.

29
00:01:37,254 --> 00:01:39,571
Who does things
without conscience?

30
00:01:39,571 --> 00:01:42,929
Generally,
they’re called animals.

31
00:01:43,586 --> 00:01:46,798
The animals,
they’re not crying

32
00:01:46,798 --> 00:01:52,895
when they’re eating 
the babies of others,

33
00:01:52,895 --> 00:01:54,364
they’re not stopping to think,

34
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:58,044
“Oh, these babies are so cute,
why should we do this?”

35
00:01:58,044 --> 00:02:00,672
Never.

36
00:02:00,672 --> 00:02:03,676
There was a YouTube video recently,
where they say,

37
00:02:03,676 --> 00:02:10,034
“After this lioness killed a deer,

38
00:02:10,034 --> 00:02:12,265
and then it took the calf”,
and all the people went,

39
00:02:12,265 --> 00:02:16,219
“Oh, look! She’s taking 
the little deer calf back to her place”,

40
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:18,075
and someone else pointed out,

41
00:02:18,075 --> 00:02:21,222
“Yes, and after playing
with it for a while,

42
00:02:21,222 --> 00:02:24,671
as cats do, she’ll eat it.

43
00:02:24,671 --> 00:02:27,524
They’ll kill it and offer it
to her children.”

44
00:02:27,524 --> 00:02:31,697
So, a lack of conscience;
of considering

45
00:02:31,697 --> 00:02:36,540
why we do things;
self–restraint;

46
00:02:36,540 --> 00:02:39,714
what Aleksandr Solzhenitsyn called

47
00:02:39,714 --> 00:02:42,889
in his famous
“World Split Apart” address,

48
00:02:42,889 --> 00:02:50,883
“What is needed 
is serene voluntary self–restraint.”

49
00:02:51,437 --> 00:02:57,641
Serene voluntary self–restraint.

50
00:02:57,981 --> 00:02:59,792
That’s interesting.

51
00:02:59,792 --> 00:03:03,488
You could say
that’s the definition of tapasyā.

52
00:03:03,488 --> 00:03:06,416
As Śrīla Prabhupād
used to say,

53
00:03:06,416 --> 00:03:09,087
and has in his 
Bhāgavatam purport,

54
00:03:09,087 --> 00:03:10,421
“What is tapasyā?

55
00:03:10,421 --> 00:03:14,383
Voluntarily inconveniencing oneself

56
00:03:14,383 --> 00:03:18,942
for the sake of spiritual realisation.”

57
00:03:19,352 --> 00:03:23,285
You will be inconvenienced
by living in this world.

58
00:03:23,285 --> 00:03:26,485
We will have to suffer
by living in this world,

59
00:03:26,485 --> 00:03:29,237
it’s inevitable,
it’s unavoidable,

60
00:03:29,237 --> 00:03:33,120
but a spiritually progressive person

61
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:36,989
will voluntarily inconvenience themselves,

62
00:03:36,989 --> 00:03:40,915
will voluntarily undergo 
certain types of “suffering”

63
00:03:40,915 --> 00:03:43,971
for the sake of
spiritual advancement.

